body.p: In the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, King County.
In the Matter of the Application of Gustave Gunderson, for a writ of } Order granting Writ Habeas Corpus

On reading and filing the petition of Gustave Gunderson, duly signed, and verified by him, whereby it appears that he is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by William Cochrane, Sheriff of King County, Washington Territory, at the County Jail, in the said County of King, Territory of Washington, and stating wherein habeas corpus ought to issue:

It is ordered that a writ of habeas corpus issue out of and under the seal of the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, directed to the said William Cochrane, commanding him to have the body of the said Gustave Gunderson before me, in the court room of the said Court forthwith, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Gustave Gunderson, together with the time and cause of his detention, and that he have then and there the said writ.
Dated on the 27th day of June, 1887.
In the matter of the application of Gustave Gunderson for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED JUN 27, 1887 James Seavey, Clerk. By W.E. Ledgerwood, Deputy Clerk.
BURKE & HALLER. ATTORNEYS-AT-LAW SEATTLE, WASH. TER.
